```json
{
  "company_name": "Tipperary",
  "tagline": "Taking the guesswork out of gratitude.",
  "document_type": "Startup Pitch Deck",
  "pitch_sections": [
    {
      "section_order": 1,
      "heading": "## 1. The Problem: Tipping Fatigue & Anxiety",
      "content": "The modern dining experience ends with a moment of high friction: the tipping screen. With the rise of 'tipflation' and digital point-of-sale systems prompting 20%, 25%, or even 30% tips at counter-service cafes, consumers are suffering from tipping fatigue. Diners lack transparent, location-specific data to know what is culturally and socially expected at individual establishments. This leads to social anxiety, guilt-tipping, and ultimately, a degraded customer experience."
    },
    {
      "section_order": 2,
      "heading": "## 2. The Solution: Enter Tipperary",
      "content": "Tipperary is a crowdsourced mobile application that provides real-time, real-world data on average tip sizes for specific restaurants. By searching for an establishment in Tipperary, users instantly see the exact percentage the average diner leaves, segmented by service type (e.g., dine-in, takeout, delivery). We replace guesswork and social pressure with hard data and peace of mind."
    },
    {
      "section_order": 3,
      "heading": "## 3. How It Works",
      "features": [
        "**Geolocated Discovery**: Open the app to see restaurants near you and their average tipping percentages.",
        "**Crowdsourced Accuracy**: Users anonymously upload receipts or input their tip amounts to earn 'Good Diner' points.",
        "**Smart Suggestions**: The app adjusts expectations based on party size, day of the week, and type of service.",
        "**Expense Integration**: Seamlessly exports tipping data for business expense reports."
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_order": 4,
      "heading": "## 4. Market Opportunity",
      "content": "The restaurant industry in the US alone generates over $900 billion annually. With over 200 million adults dining out regularly, tipping is a daily financial decision. The immediate target market encompasses Millennials and Gen Z diners who heavily index on financial tracking apps and report the highest rates of tipping anxiety. By capturing just 1% of the daily dining market, Tipperary will process millions of data points a week."
    },
    {
      "section_order": 5,
      "heading": "## 5. Business Model & Monetization",
      "revenue_streams": [
        {
          "tier": "B2C Freemium",
          "description": "Free to use for basic searches. Supported by hyper-local, non-intrusive restaurant advertising."
        },
        {
          "tier": "B2C Pro ($2.99/mo)",
          "description": "Unlocks automated receipt scanning, advanced analytics on personal tipping habits, and integrations with expense software like Concur."
        },
        {
          "tier": "B2B Analytics Dashboard",
          "description": "Restaurants subscribe to access aggregated, anonymized data on how their tipping averages compare to competitors, serving as a vital tool for staff retention and customer satisfaction metrics."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_order": 6,
      "heading": "## 6. Competitive Advantage",
      "content": "While review sites like Yelp or Google Maps focus on food quality, and payment processors like Square hold closed-door data, Tipperary is the only consumer-facing platform dedicated entirely to tipping transparency. Our first-mover advantage, combined with a gamified crowdsourcing model, creates a highly defensible data moat that becomes more accurate with every user."
    },
    {
      "section_order": 7,
      "heading": "## 7. The Ask",
      "content": "We are seeking $1.5M in Seed funding. This capital will be allocated toward finalizing iOS and Android development (40%), executing our initial user acquisition strategy in three pilot markets—New York, Austin, and San Francisco (40%), and building our core team (20%). Join us in making Tipperary the standard navigational tool for the tipping economy."
    }
  ]
}
```

